cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper is about Single Image Super Resolution (SISR) using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the learning ability of the network, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of hierarchical features and feature fusion also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of memory mechanisms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses experiments on public datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
